1.Real-time data capture: Continuously collects data on project progress, resource allocation, and spending. 
2.Cost tracking: Systematically compares actual expenses to the budget to identify variances and prevent budget overruns.
3.Automated expense logging: Uses features like mobile receipt scanning and AI to automate the creation and submission of expense reports.
4.Dashboards and analytics: Presents financial and project data in a visual, interactive format for easy analysis and insight.
5.Forecasting: Analyzes spending patterns and trends to forecast future costs more accurately.
6.Scenario planning: Allows teams to simulate different scenarios to assess their financial impact and mitigate risks.   

  
  
